  <script type="text/javascript">
      var bopCSM = {
          csmAvailable: typeof window.uet === 'function',
          pageType: 'siteLayoutType',
          setCSMProp:   function (method, prop, key) {
            if (this.csmAvailable) {
                window[method](prop, key, {wb:1});
            }
          },
          fireAjaxMarker: function(marker, scope){
              if(this.csmAvailable){
                  window.uet( marker, scope );
                  window.ues( "ctb", scope, "1" );
                  window.uex( "ld", scope );
              }
          },
          fireMarker:  function (marker) {
              if(this.csmAvailable) {
                  window.uet(marker);
              }
          },
          fireMarkers: function (markers) {
              for(var i = 0; i < markers.length; i++){
                  this.fireMarker(markers[i]);
              }
          },
          checkCacheElementsByMarker: function(container, marker){
              var elements = container.getElementsByClassName(marker);

              if(elements.length > 0){
                  for (var i = 0;i < elements.length; i++) {
                      if(!elements[i].complete){
                          return;
                      }
                  }
                  bopCSM.fireMarker(marker);
              }
          },
          allElementsLoadedFromCache: function(){
              var container = document.getElementById('siteContainer');
              if(container != null) {
                  bopCSM.checkCacheElementsByMarker(container, 'af');
                  bopCSM.checkCacheElementsByMarker(container, 'cf');
              }
          } ,
          fireImageCompleteWidgetTag: function(currentCount, maxCount, csmWidgetName){
              if(currentCount === maxCount){
                  this.setCSMProp('uex', 'ld', csmWidgetName);
              }
          },
          allImagesLoaded: function(elementId, querySelector, csmWidgetName ){
              var i,
                  images,
                  imageCounter = 0,
                  imageLength = 0,
                  imageContainer = document.getElementById(elementId);

              if (!imageContainer || !this.csmAvailable) {
                return;
              }

              images = imageContainer.querySelectorAll(querySelector);
              imageLength = images.length;

              for (i = 0; i < imageLength; i++){

                if(images[i].complete){
                  imageCounter++;
                  this.fireImageCompleteWidgetTag(imageCounter, imageLength, csmWidgetName);
                } else {
                  var imageOnLoad =images[i].onload;
                  images[i].onload = function(){
                      imageCounter++;
                      bopCSM.fireImageCompleteWidgetTag(imageCounter, imageLength, csmWidgetName);
                      if(typeof imageOnLoad === 'function'){
                          imageOnLoad.apply(this, arguments);
                      }
                  }
                }
            }
          },
    };
    //Ensure every page gets at least the af and cf events
    //if other components emit these later those will take precedence
    bopCSM.fireMarker('af');
    bopCSM.fireMarker('cf');

    //Adding this function for backwards compatability, so that we can push out without breaking the page.
    function setCSMProp(method, prop, key) {
        bopCSM.setCSMProp(method, prop, key);
    }

    function csmAllImagesLoaded(elementId, querySelector, csmWidgetName){
        bopCSM.allImagesLoaded(elementId, querySelector, csmWidgetName);
    }
  </script>

<div id="loom-companion-mv3" ext-id="liecbddmkiiihnedobmlmillhodjkdmb"><div id="shadow-host-companion"></div></div><script>_satellite["_runScript1"](function(event, target, Promise) {
/*
* Return the value of URL parameter based on current window URL (document.URL)
*
* Words of result will be separated by space not '+'
*/
window.getURLParameter = function(name) {
  return decodeURIComponent((new RegExp('[?|&]' + name + '=' + '([^&;]+?)(&|#|;|$)').exec(location.search)||[,""])[1].replace(/\+/g, '%20'))||'0';
}

/*
* Return the value of URL parameter based on given URL
*/
window.getURLParameterInGivenUrl = function(name, url) {
  name = name.replace(/[\[\]]/g, "\\$&");
  var regex = new RegExp("[?&]" + name + "(=([^&#]*)|&|#|$)"), results = regex.exec(url);
  if (!results) return null;
  if (!results[2]) return '';
  return decodeURIComponent(results[2].replace(/\+/g, " "));
}
/*
 * Function to return digital paramter for abnormal URL
 * 
 * Data element(URL parameter) doesn't work for the following url:
 *  .....%26swDim=18x17%26baseIndex=200%26limit=100
 * DE would return '0' rather than the correct '200'
 */
window.getDigitalParameter = function(key) {
  var result = new RegExp(key + '=[0-9]+', 'i').exec(window.location.href);
  if (result) {
    return result[0].match(/\d+/g)[0];
  } else {
    return '0';
  }
}

/**
 * Function to return create a map where the token name is the key
 * and the token value is the value;
 * 
 * @param  {String} string "TS=1506519782|MCMID=71737113694699667193153318835712271170|MCORGID=3E135B5B54E7878E0A4C98A2%40AdobeOrg"
 * @return {Map}           "{'TS':'1506519782', 'MCMID':'71737113694699667193153318835712271170', 'MCORGID':'3E135B5B54E7878E0A4C98A2%40AdobeOrg'}"
 */
window.getTokensInGivenString = function(string) {
  var decodedString = decodeURIComponent(string);
  var elements = decodedString.split('|');
  var map = {};

  elements.forEach(function( element ){
    var elementKeyValue = element.split("=");

    if (elementKeyValue !== '' ) {
      map[elementKeyValue[0]] = elementKeyValue[1];  
    };
  })

  return map;
}

/**
 * Function to return a specific token provided by adobe's mobile sdk
 * Adobe apends url parameters to a url. the adobe_mc url parameter has
 * multiple tokens associated with it broken up by '|'. We use this method
 * to return a specific token.
 * 
 * @param  {String} tokenName    "MDMID"
 * @param  {String} string       Example: "TS=1506519782|MCMID=71737113694699667193153318835712271170|MCORGID=3E135B5B54E7878E0A4C98A2%40AdobeOrg"
 * @return {String} string       Example: "71737113694699667193153318835712271170"
 * @return {Null}   null         If not found return null
 */
window.getTokenInGivenString = function(tokenName, string) {
  var tokenMap = getTokensInGivenString(string);
  var value = tokenMap[tokenName];

  if(value !== undefined) {
    return value;
  }

  return null;
}

/*
 * Function to check whether the given parameter is undefined or empty string
 * 
 * return true if it is defined and has some value
 * otherwise return false
 */
window.isDefined = function(value) {
  return typeof(value) !== "undefined" && value !== "";
}

/*
 * Function to replace the value in a string given the position
 *
 * return a string with new value
 */
String.prototype.replaceAt = function(index, character) {
  return this.substr(0, index) + character + this.substr(index + character.length);
}

/*
 * Function to handle the cookie related to dstillery pixel
 * If the pixel existed, check the proper position according
 * to the category name to see whether to fire the pixel or not
 * and update the dstillery cookie properly
 *
 * return boolean whether to fire the pixel or not
 */
window.fireDstilleryPixel = function(name) {
  var sessionValue = _satellite.readCookie('dstillery');
  var newSessionValue = '00000';
  var index = 0;
  switch (name) {
    case 'clothing':
      index = 0;
      break;
    case 'shoes':
      index = 1;
      break;
    case 'bags':
      index = 2;
      break;
    case 'accessories':
      index = 3;
      break;
    case 'sales':
      index = 4;
      break;
    default:
      return false;
  }
  newSessionValue = newSessionValue.replaceAt(index, '1');
  if (sessionValue) {
    if (sessionValue[index] === '1') {
      return false;
    } else {
      sessionValue = sessionValue.replaceAt(index, '1');
      _satellite.cookie.set('dstillery', sessionValue);
      return true;
    }
  } else {
    _satellite.cookie.set('dstillery', newSessionValue);
    return true;
  }
}
  

/*
 * Function to return a fragmented identifier value of a URL parameter
 *
 * Example:
 * getFragmentIdentifier("my.url.com#fi1=val1,fi2=val2", "fi2") == val2
 * getFragmentIdentifier("my.url.com#fi1=val1&fi2=val2", "fi2") == val2
 */
window.getFragmentIdentifier = function(url,name) {
  return decodeURIComponent((new RegExp('#.*' + name + '=([^,\'&]*)').exec(url)||[,])[1]);
}

/*
 * Appending a pixel image to the body
 * @param src Will be set as img's src attribute
 */
window.appendPixelImage = function(src) {
  var pixelImg = document.createElement("img");
  pixelImg.setAttribute('width', 1);
  pixelImg.setAttribute('height', 1);
  pixelImg.setAttribute('src', src);
  pixelImg.setAttribute('style', 'display:none');

  document.body.appendChild(pixelImg);
}

/*
 * Append a pixel image on the next page load.
 * This is useful for solving race conditions when the page might be 
 * redirected before the pixel is loaded.
 * @param src Will be set as img's src attribute
 */
window.appendPixelImageOnLoad = function(src) {
  var imagePixelsCookie = _satellite.readCookie('appendPixelImageSrcs') || null;
  var imagePixelsSrcs = JSON.parse(decodeURIComponent(imagePixelsCookie)) || [];
  imagePixelsSrcs.push(src);
  _satellite.cookie.set('appendPixelImageSrcs',
                       encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify(imagePixelsSrcs)),
                       7);
}

/*
 * Check whether it is CN desktop website
 */
window.isCNDesktop = function() {
  return document.domain === "cn.shopbop.com";
}

/*
 * Check whether it is CN Mdot website
 */
window.isCNMdot = function() {
  return document.domain === "m.cn.shopbop.com";
}

/*
 * Get proper value for number of result per page
 */
window.getProperNumberOfResultsED = function() {
  var counter = getDigitalParameter('limit');
  var view = '100'; // default value
  if (counter != '0') { // URL has parameter
    view = counter; 
  } else {
    var counterCookie = _satellite.readCookie('bopBrowsePref');
    if (isDefined(counterCookie)) { // Cookie existed
      view = counterCookie === '40' ? '40' : '100';
    }
  } 
  return view;
}
